## DATASET QUALITY CHECKLIST

Before training, verify your dataset has good coverage:

| Category | Minimum Entries | Why |
|----------|----------------|-----|
| prompt_craft | 200+ | Core skill — translating vision to text |
| camera_work | 100+ | Shot selection and movement |
| continuity | 50+ | Multi-shot coherence |
| lighting | 50+ | Mood and atmosphere control |
| composition | 50+ | Frame balance and visual weight |
| audio_design | 30+ | Sound-image relationship |
| workflow | 30+ | Tool-specific knowledge |
| anti_patterns | 100+ | Judgment — knowing what NOT to do |

```python
# Quick coverage check
from collections import Counter
categories = Counter()
for entry in entries:
    for tech in entry.get("techniques", []):
        categories[tech["category"]] += 1
for cat, count in categories.most_common():
    print(f"  {cat}: {count}")
```
